The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport
		 Friday, March 26, 2004  IN THE CITY
				 																																																	The IFA has decided to designate National Award-winning actor Mithun Chakraborty as the ambassador for Bengal football. IFA secretary Subrata Dutta said on Thursday that the actor will be present as and when possible during the IFA-organised tournaments. He has also promised to organise football matches that will include film stars, Dutta added. Besides, the actor has promised to bring in funds for the state association. Well use him in every possible way so that the masses get more attracted to the game, Dutta added.				 																																																	 The IFA has requested the AIFF to kick off the matches in the third phase of the NFL, starting April 4, from 3:30 pm instead of 3 pm to help the players avoid playing in the heat. Mohun Bagan have requested their April 8 match against Vasco SC to be postponed by a couple of days, since three players as well coach Aloke Mukherjee will be busy with the SAF Games. 				 																																																	 West Bengal Police beat Naihati AC 25-27, 13-25, 25-16, 25-20, 15-9 in the mens state volleyball league on Thursday. Tollygunge Subhas Sangha, Jatra Shuru Sangha and Calcutta Police also won their matches.				 																																																	 Shyamol Dutta of UCO Bank won the ninth eastern region bank chess meet conducted by the state chess association. 				 																																																	 East Bengal beat Eastern Railway by 56 runs in the AN Ghosh Trophy.				 																																																	SUMMARISED SCORES				 																																																	AN GHOSH TROPHY  EB 253/5 in 45 ovs (A. Das 103, Laxmi R. Shukla 72; K. Maity 5/34). E. Rly 197/5 in 45 ovs (S. Bhattacharya 55 n.o.). EB won by 55 runs.				 																																																	CAB LEAGUE  Tollygunge Agragami 433/4. Sporting Union 233. Tolly won by 230 runs.				 																																																	HOCKEY: Beighton Cup  Punjab Sports vs Calcutta Police (CCFC, 3 pm)
